          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Medical Debt Relief Act of 2021 </b></p> <p>This bill modifies requirements related to the reporting of medical debt. Specifically, a consumer reporting agency is prohibited from adding medical debt information to a consumer credit report if the debt </p> <ul> <li>was fully paid or settled, or </li> <li>is less than a year old. </li> </ul> <p>Additionally, a debt collector must notify the consumer prior to reporting medical debt to a consumer reporting agency. </p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-02-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
